Judicial Commission of Inquiry into allegations of state capture, corruption and fraud in the public sector including organs of state 20 June 2022 The Commission would like to inform the public that due to challenges in processing Part V and VI of the Report on time for the handover to the President by 18h00 today, 20th June 2022, it has been agreed to move the event to Wednesday, 22 June 2022 the original handover date in Cape Town. The Presidency will announce the exact time for Wednesday handover. The final volumes of the Part V and VI of the report are about 1 824 pages long. The volumes themselves are seven in total. In the interest of quality and reduction of unavoidable errors and as a result of calendar logistical problems, it has become necessary to allow for a responsible and proper completion of the conclusion of the Report. The Commission apologises to the public and all concerned for this further delay. The patience and support of the public is highly appreciated. Issued by the Secretary of the Commission, 20 June 2022